*.json:
 - example IAM policies that can be used on aws.

aws-setup:
 - A script to export AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID, AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY and AWS_DEFAULT_REGION
   so i can use it on later scripts.

aws-cli-new-instance:
 - Create an instance using aws cli, then use he.net 's dns service to update
   domain mapping. Uses cloud-init.sh to initialize the new instance.
   Being mindful of aws's free tier resource, it refuses to create new instance
   if one already exists.

cloud-init.sh
 - setups caddy and an example site to launch after boot, on proper domain and using 
   TLS from letsencrypt.

